Irked by the global condemnations of his aggressive military invasion of Ukraine, President Vladimir Putin of Russia has issued an order to his military officials to place the country’s nuclear weapon in a combat-ready position to teach the world, particularly, major European powers, America and NATO a lesson as he, Putin, insists that other nations should clearly stay off the Russia-Ukraine war. Meanwhile, the office of Ukraine’s president has disclosed that a delegation would meet with Russian officials even as Moscow’s troops drew closer to Kyiv. Putin, in giving the nuclear alert directive, cited not only the alleged statements by NATO members but the hard-hitting financial sanctions imposed by the West against Russia, including the Russian leader himself. Group Alleges Smear Campaign Against Akpabio [UPDATE] Lagos State PDP Congress: Diri Charges Delegates On… Speaking at a meeting with his top officials, Putin instructed his defence minister and the chief of the military’s General Staff to put the nuclear deterrent forces in a “special regime of combat duty.” “Western countries aren’t only taking unfriendly actions against our country in the economic sphere, but top officials from leading NATO members made aggressive statements regarding our country,” Putin said in televised comments.” ; he was quoted as saying. But the U.S. Ambassador Linda Thomas-Greenfield denounced the move as a “totally unacceptable” escalation, telling “Face the Nation” on Sunday morning that the U.S. will “continue here at the United Nations and around the world to use every possible lever we have at our disposal to expose his actions.” “President Putin is continuing to escalate this war in a manner that is totally unacceptable, and we have to continue to condemn his actions in the strongest possible way,” Thomas-Greenfield said.